 :tx/rationale "Create task: AR-4: Concentration detector — spec_neighborhood_concentration(store, window) -> Vec<ConcentrationSignal>, wired into methodology_gaps (INV-GUIDANCE-021, INV-GUIDANCE-024). BACKGROUND: The trace producer (AR-2) writes :recon/trace datoms on every command. The concentration detector scans recent traces and identifies spec neighborhoods with repeated activity. When 3+ traces land in the same neighborhood within the scan window, it fires a ConcentrationSignal that the guidance system surfaces as a methodology gap. This is the key compounding mechanism — the signal strengthens with repeated activity in the same area, making it impossible to miss. APPROACH: (1) ConcentrationSignal struct: neighborhood (String — spec namespace like 'INTERFACE' or 'SEED'), trace_count (usize), related_entities (Vec<EntityId> — top-5 entities in this neighborhood), suggestion (String — 'Review: braid task search INV-INTERFACE'). (2) spec_neighborhood_concentration(store, window: usize) -> Vec<ConcentrationSignal>: scan :recon/trace-neighborhood datoms from last window transactions. Group by neighborhood. For each with count >= 3, collect related entities from :recon/trace-neighbors. (3) Wire into methodology_gaps() in guidance.rs as a new field: concentration_gaps: Vec<ConcentrationSignal>. (4) Wire into AdjustedGaps so the gap count shows in braid status: 'concentration: 5 commands in INTERFACE — 11 related tasks'. (5) Wire into seed: when concentration is active, the Constraints section prioritizes invariants from the concentrated namespace. ACCEPTANCE: (A) 0 traces → no concentration signal. (B) 3 traces in INTERFACE namespace → signal with suggestion. (C) 3 traces spread across 3 different namespaces → no signal (no concentration). (D) Concentration shows in braid status methodology gaps section. (E) Window parameter controls how far back to scan (default: 20 transactions). DEPENDS-ON: AR-2, AR-3. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/guidance.rs + crates/braid/src/commands/status.rs"
